. * --- feTR: White public enrollment ---
. di _n "=== feTR: lnwpu ~ imp_post ==="

=== feTR: lnwpu ~ imp_post ===

. cap scalar drop nplus nminus beta sumpositive sumnegative

. cap noisily twowayfeweights lnwpu leaid year imp_post, type(feTR) summary_mea
> sures

Under the common trends assumption,
the TWFE coefficient beta, equal to -0.1233, estimates a weighted sum of 208 AT
> Ts. 
152 ATTs receive a positive weight, and 56 receive a negative weight.
------------------------------------------------
Treat. var: imp_post    # ATTs      Σ weights  
------------------------------------------------
Positive weights        152         1.5412      
Negative weights        56          -0.5412     
------------------------------------------------
Total                   208         1.0000      
------------------------------------------------

Summary Measures:
TWFE coefficient (β_fe) =   -0.1233
min σ(Δ) compatible with β_fe and Δ_TR = 0:    0.0485
min σ(Δ) compatible with treatment effect of opposite sign than β_fe in all (g,
> t) cells:    0.1004
Reference: Corollary 1, de Chaisemartin, C and D'Haultfoeuille, X (2020a)


The development of this package was funded by the European Union (ERC, REALLYCR
> EDIBLE,GA N°101043899).

. local rc_fetr_w = _rc

. 
. local fetr_w_ok = 0

. if `rc_fetr_w' == 0 | `rc_fetr_w' == 402 {
.     cap local fetr_w_beta = e(beta)
.     cap mat M = e(M)
.     if _rc == 0 {
.         local fetr_w_npos = el(M,1,1)
.         local fetr_w_nneg = el(M,2,1)
.         local fetr_w_ok = 1
.     }
.     else {
.         cap local fetr_w_npos = scalar(nplus)
.         cap local fetr_w_nneg = scalar(nminus)
.         if `fetr_w_npos' != . & `fetr_w_nneg' != . {
.             local fetr_w_ok = 1
.         }
.     }
. }

. else {
.     cap local fetr_w_beta = scalar(beta)
.     cap local fetr_w_npos = scalar(nplus)
.     cap local fetr_w_nneg = scalar(nminus)
.     if `fetr_w_npos' != . & `fetr_w_nneg' != . {
.         local fetr_w_ok = 1
.     }
. }

. 
. if `fetr_w_ok' == 1 {
.     local fetr_w_pneg = 100 * `fetr_w_nneg' / (`fetr_w_npos' + `fetr_w_nneg')
